<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-08-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-08-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="151" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d151">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Loomis</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Beaupré</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-08-03"><hi rend="italic">August 3,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 26.]</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your
                            No. 67 of July 1, last, concerning the Panama Canal. It is receiving
                            consideration.</p>
                        <p>There is an error in translation in the twentieth line of the second page
                            of the note inclosed. “Dos compañías” has been translated “two
                            countries” instead of “companies.”</p>
                        <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Francis B. Loomis</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary of State.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>